io.github.utk003.json.traditional.node

Class JSONValue.PathTrace

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.utk003.json.traditional.node.JSONValue.PathTrace
  • Enclosing class:
    JSONValue

    protected static final class JSONValue.PathTrace
extends Object
    An internal utility class for tracking whether or not a JSONValue's path matches the search expression.

    A PathTrace can represent either an index in a JSON array or a key for a JSON object. If it represents an index, then KEY will be null. Otherwise, it will not be null, and additionally INDEX will always be -1. In other words, whether or not this PathTrace represents a key for a JSON object or an index for a JSON array can be uniquely determined from the nullity of the String key variable.

    Version:
    February 23, 2021
    Author:
    Utkarsh Priyam (utk003)

    • Field Detail

      • INDEX

        public final int INDEX
        The (potential) index this PathTrace represents in a JSON array.

        If this index is -1, then it means that either this index can be any valid index or this PathTrace represents an object key instead, depending on the nullity of KEY.

        If this index is not -1, then this PathTrace must necessarily represent an index, and KEY will be null.

      • KEY

        public final String KEY
        The (potential) String key this PathTrace represents for a JSON object.

        If this key is null, then this PathTrace necessarily represents an index for a JSON array.

        Otherwise, if this key is not null, then INDEX will necessarily be -1. If this key is "*", then any child of the object matches. Otherwise, the child must specifically match the value of this key.
